property.name: org.eclipse.equinox.p2.description
property.value: This feature contains the type definition for distance matrices. It provides several nodes for reading, writing and calculating distance matrices as well as nodes that operate on distance matrices, e.g. a k-medoids clustering node.

property.name: org.eclipse.equinox.p2.provider
property.value: Chair for Bioinformatics and Information Mining, Prof. Berthold, University of Konstanz, Germany

instructions.instruction: Bundle-Vendor: %providerName Bundle-SymbolicName: org.knime.features.ext.jep.source; singleton=true Bundle-Localization: plugin Bundle-Name: %pluginName Manifest-Version: 1.0 Bundle-Version: 2.0.3.0021120

property.name: org.eclipse.equinox.p2.description
property.value: This features contributes the "Math Expression" node for evaluating free form mathematical expression. The associated plugin uses source code of JEP 2.4.1, an open-source Java library for parsing and evaluating mathematical expressions, which is under the copyright of its respective authors. To retrieve the source code of the library, please go to the JEP webiste: "http://www.singularsys.com/jep/index.html".
